T*
(needed to send account related emails to my users for things such as email address verification) Tj
T*
(and password reset requests. The reasonable option that is often suggested is to use a paid) Tj
T*
(email service such as Mailgun or SendGrid. Sending emails on your own is, according to the) Tj
T*
(Internet, too difficult. Because the prospect of adding yet another dependency on Big Tech is) Tj
T*
(depressing, I decided to go against the general advice and roll my own email server. And sure,) Tj
T*
(it wasn't trivial, but it wasn't all that hard either! Are you interested in hosting your own) Tj
T*
(email server, like me? In this article I'll tell you how to go from nothing to being able to) Tj
T*
(send emails that are accepted by all the big email players. My main concern is sending, but I) Tj
T*
(will also cover the simple solution that I'm using to receive emails and replies.) Tj
